entry.def: If you are made-up, you are wearing make-up such as powder or eye shadow.

example.ex: She was made-up and ready to go...
She was beautifully made-up, beautifully groomed...

entry.def: A made-up word, name, or story is invented, rather than really existing or being true.

example.ex: It looks like a made-up word.

entry.def: If you are made-up, you are happy.

example.ex: I'll be made up if I get in the top five, that would be great.
example.tran: 要是能进入前五名我会非常高兴，那样就太好了。

means.word_mean: 1. formed or conceived by the imagination;
3. marked by the use of makeup;
4. formed by fitting or joining components together
